&lt;pre&gt;Hi everyone,
Recently the Privacy Sandbox team announced
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://privacysandbox.com/news/privacy-sandbox-update/"&gt;https://privacysandbox.com/news/privacy-sandbox-update/&lt;/a&gt;&gt; a new path
focused on elevating user choice, instead of third-party cookie
deprecation. I want to assure our stakeholders that the change in Privacy
Sandbox direction does not impact the Chrome team's investment in FedCM. We
see FedCM as valuable for improving the privacy, security and user
experience of federated sign-in experiences independently from any changes
to third-party cookies. While we expect availability of 3PCs to continue to
be a strong factor in FedCM adoption by IDPs, there are other factors as
well. FedCM is already used
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://chromestatus.com/metrics/feature/timeline/popularity/4166"&gt;https://chromestatus.com/metrics/feature/timeline/popularity/4166&lt;/a&gt;&gt; on 1%
of Chrome page loads and we continue to expect further growth. As such, we
fully intend to continue advancing FedCM's capabilities in our effort to
better meet the federated sign-in needs of more IDPs, RPs and end-users.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

Thank you,
   Rick (on behalf of the Google Chrome FedCM team)

